
 - Gulp is the "Automation tool" / "production environmental tool" used to Automate
   the Front End Tasks.

 - Gulp Given by NodeJS Platform.

Advantages Of Gulp.

1. Minification Of  JS , CSS, HTML by using Gulp Automation Script.

2. Concatination Of Files

3. Conversion Of "SAAS" & "LESS" to "CSS"

4. We Can Easily Idenifies Errors.

5. We can Perform the Unit Test Cases

6. We Can Start the Web Servers Automatically

7. Gulp Watches the Changes in HTML / CSS / JS and Reload the Browsers Automatically


Disadvantages Of Gulp.

1. More Dependencies Creates Confusion to Write the Automation Script

2. Code may not clean like Grunt

Installation Of Gulp.
-
> npm install -g gulp


Modules in Gulp
-
1. gulp-minify-html
    - used to minify the HTML Files

2. gulp-minify-css
    - used to minify the CSS Files

3. gulp-uglify
    - used to minify the "JS" Files.

4. gulp-concat
     - used to concat the Multiple Number files to Single File.

5. gulp-util
       - it will provide utility methods to perform the Automation Tasks

6. gulp
        - it will provide base platform to write the Automation Script.


    - We Can Download All Dependencies (Gulp Dependencies) By using "package.json"

    - we can install the package.json file by using following command.

      >npm install


Ex_1.
     Concatinate the JavaScript Files.

*************************
GulpDemo

    package.json

    src
        scripts
            test_one.js
            test_two.js

        dest
            script
                final.js
**************************

//import gulp module
var gulp = require("gulp");
//import gulp-concat module
var concat = require("gulp-concat");
//create the gulp task
gulp.task("concat_js_files",function(){
    //automation of task
    gulp.src("./src/script/*.js")
        .pipe(concat("final.js")
        .pipe(gulp.dest("./dest/scripts"));
});


























































